"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-09-07-olympic-bronze-medallist-rajindra-campbell-breaks-national-record-zagreb-meet\", \"text\": \"KINGSTON, Jamaica- Rajindra Campbell, who created history in Paris last month when he became the first Jamaican to win a medal in the shot put event at the Olympic Games after he claimed bronze, continued his impressive form by setting a new national record of 22.31m at Saturday's Ivan Ivancic Memorial in Zagreb, Croatia.  The 28-year-old finished third at Saturday's meet behind Americans Ryan Crouser and Payton Otterdahl who were first and second respectively.  HOUSE RULES\"}"